  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AI tools like GPT are most valuable not as replacements for human judgment but as \"pressure tools\" to expose weaknesses in writing and ideation. The author critiques early AI drafts for their polished yet shallow \"bland professional paste\" style, which masks missing decisions and lacks authentic perspective. Key strategies for effective collaboration include using AI to interrogate drafts, generate wrong quiz answers, and compress ideas, while reserving human input for structuring arguments, tone, and critical judgment. The tone is analytical and reflective, framing AI as a collaborator that reveals—not replaces—human creativity, with metaphors like \"clay\" (malleable AI output) and \"surfaces vs. structure\" (AI-generated polish vs. human depth). The intended audience is writers and educators integrating AI into content creation workflows.",
